00:02:35.300 --> 00:02:36.000
 discussion.

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:41.000
 So here Kemperimache's begin the first paragraph saying that compassion is the sincere feeling

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:46.000
 of wanting to help remove other's suffering when you see them in pain,

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:49.000
 and that there are three types of compassion.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:53.000
 The first is compassion that focuses on sentient beings.

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:56.000
 The second is compassion that focuses on ignorance.

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
 And the third is compassion without any focus at all.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:06.000
 And they go on to say that the first type of compassion is when we see others experiencing pain

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:09.000
 and we want to help them not be in pain.

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:15.000
 And then the second type of compassion is a compassion that focuses on the root cause of suffering,

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:20.000
 which is ignorance. We don't see that everything on all levels is constantly changing.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
 And so we hold on to things as if they'll last forever.

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:29.000
 And we have compassion for everyone who makes this mistake and therefore suffers.

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:33.000
 And this third type of compassion, compassion without any focus,

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:38.000
 is all-inclusive compassion that doesn't make any distinctions between objects.

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:40.000
 It includes them all.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:45.000
 So this is the deepest level of compassion in the absolute state of equanimity.

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:50.000
 By recognizing the absolute true nature, we are free from all the limitations of concepts,

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:59.000
 judgments and preferences, and compassion naturally arises beyond all desire and duality.

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:06.000
 So then we'll go to the first topic point.

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:12.000
 This is on page 45, the second in the fourth paragraph.

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:15.000
 Compassion can be divided into three types.

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:18.000
 The first is compassion that focuses on sentient beings.

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:21.000
 The second is compassion that focuses on ignorance.

00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:25.000
 And the third is compassion without any focus.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:28.000
 The first type of compassion is easy to understand.

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:33.000
 If we look closely at the painful situations that sentient beings experience,

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:38.000
 we feel compassion and want to change their miserable conditions.

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:42.000
 The second kind of compassion is directed toward a deeper level.

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:48.000
 It is compassion for the ignorance that sentient beings have about the true nature of phenomena.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:53.000
 Everything about their bodies, possessions and emotions is constantly changing.

00:04:53.000 --> 00:05:00.000
 But due to ignorance, sentient beings grasp and cling to their lives as if they will last for eons.

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
 Then, when things change, they suffer.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:09.000
 This type of compassion focuses on ignorance as the root of all suffering.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:13.000
 The third type of compassion is objectless compassion.

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:16.000
 The first two types of compassion have objects.

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:21.000
 The first has the suffering of sentient beings and the second has their ignorance.

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:24.000
 But the third type has no particular focus.

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:27.000
 It is the deepest level of compassion.

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:35.000
 It is the meditation on the absolute state of equanimity.

