 And then Kemper Rinpoche is both taught in this Manyamaka book of theirs now.

00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:36.000
 There are two truths this chapter covers. There can only be two truths.

00:38:36.000 --> 00:38:41.000
 There's not three or more. There's not one or less. There's only two.

00:38:41.000 --> 00:38:46.000
 But if you look at the two truths, this is interesting, something to think about.

00:38:46.000 --> 00:38:49.000
 If you look at the two truths of relative and absolute truth,

00:38:49.000 --> 00:38:51.000
 then they can't be the same.

00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:54.000
 Relative truth can't be the same thing as absolute truth.

00:38:54.000 --> 00:38:58.000
 Because if it was, anything we did on the relative level would lead us to enlightenment.

00:38:58.000 --> 00:39:02.000
 And it doesn't. Because I can harm people and that doesn't lead me to enlightenment.

00:39:02.000 --> 00:39:05.000
 I can't eat an apple. That doesn't mean I'm enlightened.

00:39:05.000 --> 00:39:09.000
 In another way, they can't be different either.

00:39:09.000 --> 00:39:13.000
 Because if relative level didn't lead to enlightenment, if it was totally different,

00:39:13.000 --> 00:39:16.000
 then there'd be no way to ever get enlightened.

00:39:16.000 --> 00:39:19.000
 There'd be no way for enlightened beings to communicate on the relative level.

00:39:19.000 --> 00:39:24.000
 So there's two truths, but they can't be the same and they can't be different.

00:39:24.000 --> 00:39:26.000
 And there's two.

00:39:26.000 --> 00:39:29.000
 So this is going to the second level of emptiness.

00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:31.000
 Emptiness is beyond conceptions.

00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:38.000
 No conceptual model will actually fully make sense of the emptiness nature.

00:39:38.000 --> 00:39:40.000
 It has to be realized.

00:39:40.000 --> 00:39:42.000
 It has to be realized.

00:39:42.000 --> 00:39:52.000
 You can't eat an apple with as much love and compassion and wisdom as eating that apple.

